    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA1 missense variant c.4046C>G, resulting in the p.Thr1349Arg (T1344R) substitution, has been identified in hereditary cancer screening cohorts. In a Spanish cohort from La Rioja, the variant was classified as likely benign based on the authors\u2019 interpretation of the data [PMC11495111]. In contrast, a study of ovarian cancer patients in Apulia reported the same alteration as a variant of uncertain significance (VUS) when it was detected among somatic findings without a corresponding germline confirmation, indicating uncertainty about its clinical impact [PMC8773795]. No functional assays, population frequency data, or computational predictions were provided in the extracted evidence. The divergent clinical classifications\u2014likely benign in one report and VUS in another\u2014reflect limited and inconsistent evidence regarding the pathogenic potential of BRCA1 p.Thr1349Arg. Considering the available data, the variant leans toward a benign interpretation, but the presence of a VUS designation in an independent cohort underscores residual uncertainty, and further evidence would be required to definitively resolve its clinical significance.",
    "structured_summary": {
